2946. Matrix Similarity After Cyclic Shifts
Solved
Easy
Topics
premium lock icon
Companies
Hint
You are given an m x n integer matrix mat and an integer k. The matrix rows are 0-indexed.

The following proccess happens k times:

Even-indexed rows (0, 2, 4, ...) are cyclically shifted to the left.


Odd-indexed rows (1, 3, 5, ...) are cyclically shifted to the right.


Return true if the final modified matrix after k steps is identical to the original matrix, and false otherwise.



Example 1:

Input: mat = [[1,2,3],[4,5,6],[7,8,9]], k = 4

Output: false

Explanation:

In each step left shift is applied to rows 0 and 2 (even indices), and right shift to row 1 (odd index).



Example 2:

Input: mat = [[1,2,1,2],[5,5,5,5],[6,3,6,3]], k = 2

Output: true

Explanation:



Example 3:

Input: mat = [[2,2],[2,2]], k = 3

Output: true

Explanation:

As all the values are equal in the matrix, even after performing cyclic shifts the matrix will remain the same.



Constraints:

1 <= mat.length <= 25
1 <= mat[i].length <= 25
1 <= mat[i][j] <= 25
1 <= k <= 50


Seen this question in a real interview before?
1/5




Shukriya Mat Kar Bhai — Ye Tera Haq Hai! 😄

Visual Algorithm — Poora Flow
Input: mat, k
         ↓
Step 1: k % colLen
(effective shifts nikalo)
         ↓
    k == 0?
    ↙      ↘
  YES       NO
   ↓         ↓
return     Step 2:
 true    Har row check karo
              ↓
         i % 2 == 0?
         ↙        ↘
       EVEN        ODD
     (left)      (right)
        ↓            ↓
   mat[i][j]    mat[i][j]
      ==            ==
 mat[i][j+k]  mat[i][j-k]
      ↓            ↓
     NO?          NO?
      ↓            ↓
   return       return
    false        false
         ↓
   Loop khatam
         ↓
     return true

Kyun Yeh Algo Kaam Karta Hai — 3 Pillars
Pillar 1 — Cyclic Property
n shifts = original wapas
isliye k % n = actual useful shifts
Pillar 2 — In-Place Comparison
Nayi array banane ki zaroorat nahi!
Original matrix mein hi check karo —
"Jo j pe hai, woh shift ke baad bhi
 same position pe hona chahiye"
Pillar 3 — Boundary Handling
Left:  (j+k) % m       → overflow rok
Right: (j-k+m) % m     → negative rok

Real Life Se Example 😄
Soch — 10 log circle mein khade hain
Sab 3 step aage badhte hain

Kya circle same dikhega?
→ Sirf tab jab 3 % 10 == 0  (nahi dikhega)
→ Ya sab same value hain    (dikhega)

Yahi matrix mein ho raha hai! 🎯
